name: Rhubarb Upside Down Cake II
author: TOMBO
summary: A fun summer cake for kids to help make, using fresh rhubarb, strawberry gelatin, marshmallows and cake mix. When you cut it and take it out of the pan, flip the piece over so the rhubarb is on top.
ingredients: 1 (3 ounce) package strawberry flavored Jell-O® mix
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Spread butter in the bottom of a 9x13 inch pan
Spread the rhubarb in an even layer on the bottom of the pan
Sprinkle with sugar, and then with the strawberry gelatin mix
Cover with an even layer of miniature marshmallows
Prepare the cake mix according to package instructions
Bake in the preheated oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean
